# Deferred GitHub save

- Do **not** commit or push to GitHub after every change or every user request.
- Only save to GitHub after the user **stops making requests** and **10 minutes** pass with no new user request.
- When finishing work that leaves a dirty tree, arm a **one-shot 10-minute** deferred save (`Start-Sleep -Seconds 600` + `AGENT_LOOP_WAKE_deferred_git`). Cancel/replace any previous deferred-save timer first.
- On wake: if there are uncommitted changes, commit as `TeodorDriz3r` / `TeodorDriz3r@users.noreply.github.com` and push to `origin`. If clean, do nothing.
- If the user sends a new request before the 10 minutes end, cancel the old timer and re-arm 10 minutes after the next change batch (or after the reply if the tree is still dirty).
- Local preview (`localhost`) and opening the site are fine anytime; GitHub push waits for the idle window.
